I stand against the chaos and the cross of holy fire&quot; - N. Peart</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kathodos>Kathodos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 272<br> <font color=#333333>(11/8/02 1:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=811.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.battle.net/war3/images/human/units/animations/waterelement.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: 57 Earth? what's wrong with that one?</span><hr size=1> Earth will root the mobs quite successfully.<br>
<br>
This means it's great for chain casting pets (allows you some safety) but horrible if you want the mob to turn and run.  Instead of turning to run, the mob will continue to beat upon the pet until one of them dies, which is a considerable amount more damage for a mob that normally runs when at 15 - 20% health. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style=""><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=59365">Kathodos</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - Battle Cleric of Tunare - Tholuxe Paells</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style=""><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=59365">Kantreach</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - Arch Mage Antagonist - Tholuxe Paells</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=limpylionbait>LimpyLionBait</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 227<br> <font color=#333333>(11/9/02 2:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=811.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  /agree</span><hr size=1> Hmm could you summon up some of our cancel magic staves and use it on the mob when it turns to flee but gets rooted? Cant remember how many charges it has, but its got to be cheaper mana-wise than healing the extra punishment the pet takes when the mob cant flee.<br>
<br>
Maybe use our first super cheap cancel magic spell instead of the stave...<br>
<br>
Heh equip pet with that iron bound tome or whatever its called that procs cancel magic  :P Those are rather cheap in the bazaar - I couldnt even give one away when I had one - from Kaesora I think.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=izudin@themagicianstower>Izudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 192<br> <font color=#333333>(11/9/02 9:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=811.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Earth pet in Velks</span><hr size=1> One good spot (theoretically) to use the earth pet would be Velks, cause mobs never run here at low health. However the spiders have a cold based attack (Velium Poison) which WILL hit the earth pet often if you dont have a real high cold resist.<br>
<br>
I tried both earth and air here and found air more convenient, for one because of its near immunity to cold (its really really rare for the air pet to get velium poisoned) and also for its higher damage avoidance.<br>
<br>
I think one of the early documents about magicians stated that the real weakness of the earth pet was its low agility. I never tested this, but maybe a good shaman agility buff could help the earth pet.<br>
<br>
Izudin<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tangting>TangTing</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 168<br> <font color=#333333>(11/9/02 5:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=811.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  57 Earth Pet</span><hr size=1> Brutal beatdowns are a fact of life with earth pets.  So, for the soloing non-chaincaster, is there any reason not to use the air pets?  Any specific situations that strongly favor the V/GV water, fire, or earth pets in a solo situation? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ssslippy>SSSlippy</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 373<br> <font color=#333333>(11/9/02 9:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=811.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  ds</span><hr size=1> Since the earth pet gets hit alot more often then any other pet the damage shield on the pet plays a huge roll.  Make sure you put a damage shield on your pet and he will be able to destroy things. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tangting>TangTing</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 175<br> <font color=#333333>(11/10/02 8:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=811.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Earth Pet</span><hr size=1> I've DS'ed the earth pet, but the cost/benefit just hasn't been worth it for me.  I like to summon one pet, give it armor and stick with it.  When I use the Earth pet I spend a lot of downtime waiting for the the pet to regen. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eloinapyromancer>Eloina Pyromancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 133<br> <font color=#333333>(11/11/02 12:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=811.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Earth Pet</span><hr size=1> You've answered your own question.<br>
<br>
I use earth pets whenever I have mobs that I don't want to see run, and where I want to reclaim/recast at the end of the fight.  My ideal for a 57 earth is a mob where the pet kills the mob with about 5% hp's to spare.  I reclaim and recast, and I'm ready for the next.<br>
<br>
I don't use armor on earth, what's the point?  I don't give him weapons or anything else.  I may give him a muzzle, but usually not.  He's summoned, BO/DS, fights, reclaim, recast.<br>
<br>
If I'm chaincasting, I use 51 or 49 earth and make sure I stick malosini to make up for the level difference.  51 earth costs 300 mana, 49 costs 200.  The only reason to use 51 earth is for the dmg dealing root spell, which can add up fairly nicely.  I never use 57 earth for chaining, since the extra 200-300 hps doesn't make up for the extra 100 mana it costs to summon him.<br>
<br>
Otherwise, if I want my pet to stick around for awhile, I use air or water, depending on my tactics.<br>
<br>
BTW, I've seen very little benefit to giving a pet armor.  Parsing logs with armor and without, it seems like less than a 5% difference between the two on damage taken. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=euphorion>Euphorion</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 197<br> <font color=#333333>(11/11/02 9:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=811.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   ok ok ;-)</span><hr size=1> Well....Zyphyr said something really correct<br>
&quot;Surely you haven't forgotten that already.&quot;<br>
<br>
I really havent used earth pets often. I used it at 24 when I didnt have the other research only pets and I used it at 51-53. The 51 earth did do really well as far as I can remember against the &quot;normal&quot; Mobs in SD. Thats why I was a bit &quot;shocked&quot; now I think... <br>
<br>
Anyway...<br>
Meanwhile I like the GVoc Earth ;-)<br>
53 Air allowed me to solo 9-10 Tro Jegs per spawn cycle.<br>
Now when I for the first time in my whole mage life am really chaining Pet I manage to kill 12-14 per spawn cycle.<br>
<br>
And I also can imagine what happend during the first test. I was probably just &quot;double unlucky&quot;.<br>
Among the several Tro Jeg &quot;types&quot; there's one which can be really nasty.<br>
I think I did the tries against that type and probably the Mob even got lucky with Procs and stuff.<br>
<br>
But it's not too rare that I start the new Pet when the old one is still at 40% health and still the old one dies before the new one is finished.<br>
<br>
Anyway...meanwhile fighting with GVoc Earth really works out well. <br>
The camp isn't as relaxing as before anymore (I always have to do something now ;-) ) but exp is of course much better than before ,-) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tangting01>TangTing01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#333333>(11/14/02 9:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=811.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ok ok ;-)</span><hr size=1> Eloina,<br>
I give the pet armor as a matter of habit, but I have had the question of whether it makes any difference.  I haven't done any formal parses, but I never seemed to notice much, if any, difference.<br>
<br>
I really, really don't want to start chaincasting, but it seems like it is becoming a more common technique.  Maybe I'll practice for a bit.  Question for chaincasters - how often does it go wrong?  Do you have a macro social button or do you manually type &quot;pet get lost&quot; every time? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=marloon>Marloon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#333333>(11/14/02 10:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=811.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   RE:</span><hr size=1>  Well, for chain casting, it all depends on the caster. I know i have had a few go wrong but never lost my life doing it.  A couple of mistakes I have made is hitting the get lost button too late.  Thus you get the You can't have more then one pet, or some such thing, right as you hit the button then you have no pet.  Also, sometimes my pet will die as I am casting and for some odd reason I still hit the pet go away button, after my new pet is formed.  Sounds stupid but you get so used to hitting that button at some point during that cast that(atleast for me) it didn't sink in that I didn't have to &quot;go away&quot; anymore that time.  That doesn't happen anymore thank god.  <br>
<br>
  If you have the new UI, theres a button on your pet menu that says go away.  You can click that while casting.  The only thing is sometimes you get a little delay before it goes in. This is rarely but you'll want to hit the button a little earlier.  The safer way is to type it in. If you do it that way it's instant and you can cut it a lot closer.  Either way that it feels right for you.<br>
<br>
  Now what most people chain cast seems to be the earth pet.  I totally agree that that pet is a great chaining pet due to it's high hitpoints. <br>
<br>
